        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 8:45AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 845 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Greenville Downtown, or over Berea, moving east at 45
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greenville Downtown, Greenville Eastside, West Greenville, Greer,
Mauldin, Taylors, Berea, Five Forks, Welcome, and Travelers Rest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
